          "skill_notes": "Regular healing heals the three lowest HP allies by 44.6% of ATK.<br>Mystic Flour Cookie's immunity to incapacitating debuffs includes debuffs that bypass Immunity or resistance to interrupting effects, such as Petrification or status{Light_Cage|und_debuff} Light Cage. It also grants immunity to Pull effects. However, it does not prevent status{Silence} Silence, Knockback effects, or Flying effects.<br>* Mystic Flour Cookie still receives debuffs inflicted onto targets immune to certain incapacitating debuffs, such as status{Drowsy} Drowsy or status{Chill|und_debuff} Chill.<br>color-header{D9C398:Realm of Apathy}<br>Mystic Flour Cookie becomes immune to ATK SPD changes and resists interrupting effects while using the skill.<br>Mystic Flour Cookie remains in place while using her skill unless used out of combat, and becomes immune to most displacement effects while Realm of Apathy is active.<br>status{DMG_Down} DMG Resist granted to self from this skill is undispellable.<br>color-header{D9C398:Cocoon of Futility}<br>Cocoon of Futility is indicated by a white border overlaying the HP bars of affected allies. Any additional effects visible on the HP bar such as cookie{Shining_Glitter} Shining Glitter Cookie's Glittering Rock Spirit or status{Injury|und_debuff} Injury are hidden until the effect expires.<br>Cocoon of Futility purifies any status{Apathy|und_debuff} Apathy debuff on the Cookie and prevents its application, but cannot recover any HP reduced by Apathy.<br>color-header{D9C398:Pale Plague}<br>The Pale Plague debuff applies a floury-dust overlay on targets that it affects.<br>The initial effect that increases Cooldown is separate from the Pale Plague debuff, and can be applied to targets with status{Immunity} Immunity or status{Invulnerable|und_buff} Invulnerable.<br>If the Pale Plague debuff is blocked by Immunity or Invulnerable, the Cooldown-increase effect triggered by purifying Pale Plague from the target will still be activated.<br>Cooldowns cannot be increased beyond their post-Cooldown Reduction-calculated value.<br>A separate status{ATK_SPD_Down} ATK SPD Down debuff is applied on targets without Cooldowns, including Cookie enemies.<br>color-header{FFD073:Lantern of Apathy}<br>At the beginning of the battle, Mystic Flour Cookie summons the Lantern of Apathy to accompany the team. It is uninteractable with any other units or effects.<br>If Mystic Flour Cookie is defeated then revived at a later time, the extra effects for Lantern of Apathy are reverted.<br>status{DMG_Down} DMG Resist gained from Cooldown and status{Max_HP_Up} Max HP Up are undispellable.<br>-38% Cooldown is needed to reach the maximum DMG Resist.<br>* External cooldown reduction from sources such as Treasures or game mode effects will not increase the DMG Resist gained from this effect."
